ZCZC GE02
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 072300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING HIGH PRESSURE CENTRED NEAR THE SERN BALTIC AROUND 1030.
A BROAD LOW COMPLEX OVER THE N ATLANTIC SW OF ICELAND EXTENDS TOWARDS THE
NORWEGIAN SEA. THROUGH THE PERIOD THE BALTIC HIGH SOON DECLINES SE. THE
BROAD LOW COMPLEX REMAINS TO THE N AND NW OF THE BRITISH ISLES WITH OCCASIONAL
LOW CENTRES WITHIN THE COMPLEX SWINGING E BUT MAINLY N OF MAINLAND BRITAIN.
A SMALL DEEPER LOW MAY MOV NE ACROSS THE UK ON WEDNESDAY BUT THIS CARRIES
LOW CONFIDENCE. BY THURSDAY LOW PRESSURE BROADLY RESIDES TO THE N OF THE
REGION WITH HIGHER PRESSURE TO THE S. STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS ACROSS
NERN CULLERCOATS MONDAY EVENING EXTENDING INTO CENTRAL PARTS OF THE N SEA
INTO TUESDAY BEFORE EASING LATER. A FURTHER SWATHE OF STRG WINDS WITH OCCASIONAL
NEAR GALE AND PERHAPS LOCAL GALES TRANSFERS NE ACROSS THE N SEA WEDNESDAY
ONLY SLWY EASING INTO THURSDAY BUT REMAINING STRG IN THE N
